h1.span: - applyingMasksToValidationAreas.R : takes the process 2mile square validataion are and applied the forest urban area masks
- carbonAccountingVector.R : a sample workflow for testing the probabilistic flip methodology

div.div: ; generate the change over time data produces, produces a riparian mask layer. Adapataions are present for additional of harmonized models.
- checkForFullStateModels : A helper script to trouble shoot where is the processing method model areas are missing data
Downloaded exported model data from google drive, Generates a single image file for each model grid, apply riparian and urban masks, output feeds into changeOverTime.R
- determineSampleArea.R : does a random select of 2 mile sample grids
-downloadHarmonizedModels.R : Download and formats the harmonized model results
- generateMapsOfHarmonizedImages.R : produces 2x2 plot of harmonized images for qualitative assessments
- generateSubGridForValidation.R : produces the 2x2 mile subgrid plot using the COT imagery
- grapAndProcessCSB.R : preprocess on vector based crop data.

h1.span: - grabTopPredictors.R : helper script for visualizing model parameters for "b" model

div.span: - moveCleanUpimages.R : helper script for placing reran models into the correct location
- organizeSamplingGrids.R : generates the rank order grids based on the quantitative assessments
- pointValidation.R : using the training data to produce a confusion matrix; evaluated but did not use
- prepTreeHeightData.R : developed an example of tree height datal; evaluated did not use
- processNLCDDatasets.R : produce yearly images for total canopy cover and forested areas from the NLCD data
- reclassByYear.R : helper funtion to reclass the change over time images
- selectionHarminonizedModels.R : evaluates all four models to select those with the lowest total tree cover
- stage1.rmd ; alternative to the 0b_runR_processes.R, used to prep data for modeling step
- templateCarbonAccountingWorkflow.R : example workflow to show the options for montecarlo analysis
- reclassTo10.R : method for producing the 10m version of the model outputs
